            <commentid>1980</commentid>
            <who name="Ralf Sternberg">rsternberg</who>
            <bug_when>2007-07-11 11:32:49 +0200</bug_when>
            <thetext>When a text area has a padding (as defined in the classic appearance), the scroll bars are also positioned within this padding. 
Example:

  var text = new qx.ui.form.TextArea();
  text.setSpace( 10, 75, 10, 75 );
  text.setValue( &quot;Lorem ipsum dolor sit amet, consectetuer adipiscing elit.&quot; );
  text.addToDocument();

There should be a way to apply a padding to text areas that does not affect the scroll bars.</thetext>
          </long_desc>
